Went with my husband and 3 kids (one is a 15mo old toddler) to the Gilbert location.  After reading the reviews about the wilted salad lettuce and hit or miss sides, I was a little nervous. My salad was awesome, I think that bad salad review was a year ago, so I guess they hear us. The ribs were so tender and falling off the bone, the beef brisket was good too. The smoked chicken wasn't my favorite, we took that home as left overs and it tasted better the next day...who knew? The fried corn on the cob was great too. The coleslaw  & baked potato was average. The decor was funny, filled with silly signs about humanity and hogs  I really, really, really, loved their sauces! Will definitely go back soon.

